<%- include('partials/head') %>
<%- include('partials/header') %>

<main class="container">
  <h2 class="section-title">Heritage & Story</h2>

  <!-- Narrative Section 1 -->
  <section class="brand-story-teaser" style="margin-top: 40px; border-top: none;">
    <div class="brand-story-grid">
      <div class="brand-story-text">
        <span style="font-size: 0.75rem; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--accent-color); letter-spacing: 0.15em; display: block; margin-bottom: 15px;">The Philosophy</span>
        <h3>Sculpting Silhouettes, Preserving Time</h3>
        <p>
          Founded in London, Thistlewood was established to redefine classical English heritage tailoring for the modern era. We treat garment construction not as factory logistics, but as physical architecture. 
        </p>
        <p>
          By creating bespoke patterns, drafting structured silhouettes directly onto heavy heritage fabrics, and finishing seams with hand-sewn invisible stitches, we design garments that develop a singular dialogue with the wearer's body over decades.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="brand-story-image">
        <img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1539571696357-5a69c17a67c6?q=80&w=800&auto=format&fit=crop" alt="Tailored fitting portrait" loading="lazy">
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Narrative Section 2 -->
  <section class="brand-story-teaser" style="margin-top: 0; border-top: none; border-bottom: none;">
    <div class="brand-story-grid" style="grid-template-columns: 1fr 1.2fr;">
      <div class="brand-story-image">
        <img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1509631179647-0177331693ae?q=80&w=800&auto=format&fit=crop" alt="Premium tweed and wool swatches" loading="lazy">
      </div>
      <div class="brand-story-text" style="max-width: 550px;">
        <span style="font-size: 0.75rem; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--accent-color); letter-spacing: 0.15em; display: block; margin-bottom: 15px;">Artisanal Sourcing</span>
        <h3>The Noble Origin of Fibers</h3>
        <p>
          Our sourcing process is deliberate. We partner exclusively with historic textile mills in Yorkshire and the Shetland Islands for our signature heavy wools, tweeds, and flannels, ensuring every weave carries centuries of British textile expertise.
        </p>
        <p>
          We trace every bale of virgin wool and cashmere from shearer to spinner. These materials are chosen because they possess a physical weight, structure, and drape that mass-produced synthetic fibers can never replicate.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Narrative Section 3 -->
  <section class="brand-story-teaser" style="margin-top: 0; border-bottom: none;">
    <div class="brand-story-grid">
      <div class="brand-story-text">
        <span style="font-size: 0.75rem; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--accent-color); letter-spacing: 0.15em; display: block; margin-bottom: 15px;">Studio Details</span>
        <h3>Hand-Finished in London</h3>
        <p>
          Thistlewood operates out of a historic design studio on Savile Row, London. Here, a dedicated circle of master cutters, pattern-drafters, and tailors bring each seasonal collection to life. 
        </p>
        <p>
          Each jacket, trench coat, or pleated trouser is assigned to a single tailor from initial cut to final stitch. The signature labels sewn inside are hand-numbered to represent this focused, individual attention.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="brand-story-image">
        <img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1512436991641-6745cdb1723f?q=80&w=800&auto=format&fit=crop" alt="Structured wool coats hanging on rack" loading="lazy">
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</main>

<%- include('partials/footer') %>
